
Overview of noun folly

The noun folly has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) folly, foolishness, unwiseness -- (the trait of acting stupidly or rashly)
2. (1) stupidity, betise, folly, foolishness, imbecility -- (a stupid mistake)
3. folly, foolishness, craziness, madness -- (the quality of being rash and foolish; "trying to drive through a blizzard is the height of folly"; "adjusting to an insane society is total foolishness")
4. folly, foolery, tomfoolery, craziness, lunacy, indulgence -- (foolish or senseless behavior)
